<doc id="32461" wikidata="Q3395229" url="?curid=32461" title="Foreign relations of Venezuela">
<text>The foreign relations of Venezuela had since the early twentieth century been particularly strong with the United States. However, since the election of Hugo Chávez as President of Venezuela in 1998, Venezuela&#x27;s foreign policy differed substantially from that of previous Venezuelan governments. This change in foreign policy direction continues under the current president Nicolás Maduro.

From 2019 to 2023, Juan Guaidó disputed the presidency of Venezuela. And Edmundo González since the 2024 venezolan elections. 

== Diplomatic relations ==
